<item>
            <title>[SWF-1440] JSF 2.0 support in portlet environments</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SWF-1440</link>
                <project id="10050" key="SWF">Spring Web Flow</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi all,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently I am using Spring Webflow 2.2.1 with JSF 1.2 (together with Primefaces 1.2) in a portlet environment.&lt;br/&gt;
The features of JSF 2.0 compelling. So I asked myself if it would be possible to make us of JSF 2.0.&lt;br/&gt;
Unfortunately it is not possible due to the fact that Webflow respects JSR-329 that only covers JSF 1.2 in a portlet environment. JSR-329 does not talk about JSF 2.0, it is even not yet planed to work on JSF 2.0 integration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I asked myself if it would be possible that Spring Source takes some effort in this direction before the (slow) community does.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am assured that this is an obvious requirement to all those who want to use JSF within a portlet environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Florian&lt;/p&gt;</description>
